[DONE] call/cc — ESCAPE continuations (one-shot, upward). (call/cc f) calls f
       with k; (k v) makes call/cc return v, abandoning the work between. Full
       re-entrant continuations aren't feasible in a recursive C tree-walker +
       bytecode VM without a CPS/stack-copy rewrite, so this is the escape-only
       subset (like Scheme call/ec); k is valid only in call/cc's dynamic
       extent. Mechanism: (k v) yields an EXP_ERROR-tagged escape token
       (ERROR_CONT_ESCAPE, id in meta, payload in next) that propagates up the
       existing error plumbing to the matching call/cc frame. No setjmp.
       Implementing it surfaced + fixed TWO pre-existing bugs: (1) whilecmd
       swallowed body errors/escapes (re-eval'd the condition over them →
       (while true (/1 0)) would spin); (2) OP_TAIL_CALL's in-place TCO reused
       the caller's env for a CLOSURE tail-callee, resolving the closure's
       captured free vars wrong — now real (non-global) closures route through
       vm_invoke_values (top-level defs keep TCO). Tests "20g" in test.alc.
[DONE] MessagePack codec: (msgpack-encode v) -> blob, (msgpack-decode blob)
       -> value. Covers nil, t, fixnums (fixint/uint/int 8-64), floats
       (float32 decode, float64), strings/symbols (fixstr/str8-32), blobs
       (bin8-32), lists (fixarray/array16-32), string-keyed dicts
       (fixmap/map16-32); chars encode as int codepoint. Big-endian,
       bounds-checked decode. Errors (encode: unsupported type; decode:
       malformed/truncated/non-string key/trailing data) are catchable.
       Self-contained codec (alcove.c, like the savedb serializer); tests
       "20i" in test.alc.
