[DONE] HAMT / persistent map (EXP_HAMT): immutable map with structural
       sharing (32-way bitmap trie, 5 hash bits/level, collision buckets).
       Refcounted C nodes shared across versions (acyclic DAG → no cycles).
       Builtins: hamt, hamt-assoc, hamt-get (w/ default), hamt-dissoc,
       hamt-count, hamt-contains?, hamt-keys, hamt-vals, hamt->list (flat
       k v ...), hamt-merge (b wins), hamt?. Wired into print ({k v, ...}),
       istrue, unrefexp free, isatom. Tests "20f" in test.alc (incl.
       immutability, overwrite, 300-insert scale, mixed key types, merge,
       deep iso equality, savedb persistence); ASan-clean, version-churn RSS
       flat. `iso` compares two HAMTs by content (order-independent, deep);
       `is` stays identity. savedb/loaddb round-trips a HAMT (type+count then
       recursive key/value dump via dump_hamt_value/load_hamt_value), incl.
       nested values. NOT yet: apply-compat (apply doesn't compose with
       builtins — orthogonal).
       Ref: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_array_mapped_trie ;
       clojure PersistentHashMap ; chaelim/HAMT ; Ctries (lock-free).
