[DONE] BUG: (filter pred (cdr xs)) inside a recursive fn evaluated to
       blank. ROOT CAUSE (not refcount): (cdr <1-element list>) returns
       C NULL (lists terminate with NULL, not NIL_EXP), and filter/map/
       reduce/any?/all?/sort-by guarded `if (!fn || !xs)` — rejecting the
       NULL list as a missing parameter and erroring. Fix: require the
       list-arg FORM (arity) but treat a NULL VALUE as the empty list.
       Regression tests "filter inside recursion" + per-builtin
       "(cdr 1-elem)" cases in test.alc.

[TODO] Reserved-name shadowing: lookup() checks reserved_symbol BEFORE
       env, so `(= time (ffi-fn ...))` doesn't take effect at top level
       (alcove's builtin time wins). Either flip lookup order or
       provide an explicit "shadow" form.

[DONE] FFI callbacks: (ffi-callback RET (ARG-TYPES...) fn) wraps an alcove
       lambda in a libffi closure (ffi_closure_alloc/ffi_prep_closure_loc)
       and returns a value passable where a ptr arg is expected. C can call
       back into alcove — incl. in a loop, with double args, and closures
       that capture free vars. Ret/arg types: void int long double ptr (no
       string return — buffer lifetime). Portable (libffi owns the
       executable trampoline; no arch code). Example ffi-examples/05.
[DONE] FFI struct-by-value: (ffi-struct field-types...) defines a by-value
       aggregate (scalar fields int/long/double/ptr); usable as an ffi-fn
       arg/return type. (ffi-pack desc vals...) -> blob laid out per the C
       ABI; (ffi-unpack desc blob) -> field-value list. Manual scalar-
       aggregate layout (matches the C ABI on all libffi targets; no
       dependency on ffi_get_struct_offsets). Struct args pass blob bytes;
       struct returns wrap the bytes in a blob. Verified: struct arg, struct
       return, 2-in-1-out, mixed int/double fields, ASan-clean under churn.
       Example ffi-examples/06.
[DONE] FFI nested structs: a struct descriptor is a valid ffi-struct field
       type (struct-in-struct). Parent layout uses the nested size/alignment;
       pack memcpy's the nested blob into the field slot; unpack yields the
       nested bytes as a blob (ffi-unpack again with the nested descriptor).
       Tested via alc_ffi_selftest_seg + example 06. Still NOT done: string
       struct fields (use ptr).
[DONE] FFI varargs: (ffi-vfn lib name ret fixed-arg-types...) binds a
       variadic C function (e.g. printf). The fixed prefix is declared; extra
       call args have their type inferred (fixnum->long, float->double,
       char->int, string/nil->pointer) and the cif is built per call via
       ffi_prep_cif_var. The "Apple-arm64 wall" turned out STALE — verified
       working on macOS arm64 with libffi 3.4 (a snprintf/printf smoke test
       plus alc_ffi_selftest_vsum/vsumd in the suite). Tests in test.alc's
       FFI block; example ffi-examples/07. NOT covered: struct/callback as a
       variadic arg (variadic tail is scalar only).

[DONE] MEMORY LEAK: closure↔captured-env refcount cycle. A def/let closure
       created INSIDE a function body leaked, scaling with closures created
       (top-level defs immune). Root cause was TWO compounding bugs: (1) a
       per-call refcount leak — evaluate's (operator args) dispatch leaked
       the owned tmpexp2 ref after the non-tail invoke (every sibling branch
       released it; the invoke branch forgot), pinning env-resolved closures;
       (2) the genuine lambda↔env 2-cycle. Fix: add the missing
       unrefexp(tmpexp2) + env_break_self_cycle() in destroy_env (Option B,
       conservative guards). Repro 120MB→2MB flat; 951/0 + ASan-clean.
       Full writeup in docs/closure_env_cycle_leak.md; tests "20c" in
       test.alc.

[DONE] security/memory audit (2026-05): fixed FFI ->ptr crash (ffi-fn arg
       type read raw union as a pointer → SIGSEGV; now exp_text), RESP
       write-buffer DoS ceiling (RESP_WBUF_MAX + wfail drop), unchecked
       reallocs → graceful_shutdown, KEYS* partial-OOM double-free,
       make_inline_txt negative-length guard, non-Apple JIT W^X (mprotect
       W→RX), and vec int32 capacity overflow/UB. deserializer + core
       refcount model audited clean.

[DONE] Compile lambda for closures (was AST-only). Closures now compile
       to bytecode with bc->no_gcache set, so OP_LOAD_GLOBAL/CALL_GLOBAL
       do a fresh env-chain lookup each time instead of a per-bc gcache
       hit (which would serve stale values for a captured var). Closures
       are not JIT'd (the JIT global-call helpers cache).

[DONE] Compile mutating-free-var closures (OP_STORE_FREE). `=`/`setf` to
       a non-slot target (a captured free var or a global) used to fail
       compilation and fall back to AST. New OP_STORE_FREE op +
       assign_store_symbol() walk the env chain at runtime, mutating the
       nearest existing binding (else creating in the CURRENT env — the
       only difference from setq_store_symbol, which creates in root),
       so make-counter and friends now compile fully. Also fixed: the
       compile_lambda param loop refused 0-arg bodies (empty params `()`
       = nil_singleton with NULL content, misread as a malformed param);
       now matches var2env's `p->content` guard, so 0-arg fns compile.
       Reserved-name assignment is rejected at runtime by OP_STORE_FREE,
       same as OP_SETQ_DYN.

[DONE] OP_MOD bytecode op + JIT shape for (fn (a b) (is (mod a b) K))
       — divides? was running as AST because mod was an unrecognized
       builtin. Now: mod is one bytecode op; divides? compiles to 10
       bytes + JITs to ~70 bytes of native (idiv + cmovz). sieve raw
       17ms → 6ms.
[DONE] (any? pred list) and (all? pred list) builtins — walk in C
       with one vm_invoke_values per element. Useful when called
       outside recursive contexts; see TODO below for the bug that
       limits use inside.

[DONE] BUG: (do (fn-call) other) lost `other`, breaking recursion.
       No longer reproduces — both the (g 5) and (any? ...) repros now
       recurse fully (verified => 4). Resolved by the closure/do-body
       compilation work (these fns now compile to bytecode instead of
       hitting the AST flow bug). Regression tests "do: call then tail
       recurse" and "do: any? then tail recurse" in test.alc.

[WATCH] possible (def f () ...) body-form drop when body is a (case ...)
